<div class="core-journal-description"><div property="isPartOf" typeof="Periodical"><span property="name">RadioGraphics</span></div><div class="core-enumeration"><span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationVolume">Volume <span property="volumeNumber">29</span></span> • <span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationIssue">Number <span property="issueNumber">3</span></span> • <span property="datePublished">May 1 2009</span></div><div class="core-pagination"><span class="heading">Pages</span>: <span class="content"><span property="pageStart">781</span> - <span property="pageEnd">789</span></span></div><div class="core-pmid"><span class="heading">PubMed</span>: <a class="content" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/19448115/" property="sameAs" target="_blank" title="Link to PubMed">19448115</a></div></div></div></section><section class="core-copyright"><h4>Copyright</h4><div role="paragraph">© RSNA, 2009.</div></section><section class="core-history"><h4>History</h4><div><b class="core-label">Published online</b>: May 1 2009</div></section><section class="core-permissions"><h4>Permissions</h4><div>Request permissions for this article.</div><div><a class="btn" href="https://marketplace.copyright.com/rs-ui-web/mp/search/all/10.1148%2Frg.293085120">Request Permissions</a></div></section><section property="keywords"><h4>Keywords</h4><ol><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=CAF+%3D+coronary+artery+fistula&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">CAF = coronary artery fistula</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=LCA+%3D+left+coronary+artery&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">LCA = left coronary artery</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=MIP+%3D+maximum+intensity+projection&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">MIP = maximum intensity projection</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=MPA+%3D+main+pulmonary+artery&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">MPA = main pulmonary artery</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=RCA+%3D+right+coronary+artery&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">RCA = right coronary artery</a></li></ol></section><section class="core-article-notes"><h4>Notes</h4><div role="paragraph">The different types of coronary artery fistulas are discussed and illustrated, with emphasis on the common anatomic sites and the cross-sectional imaging features.</div></section></section><section id="tab-contributors" role="tabpanel"><h3>Authors</h3><section class="core-authors"><h4>Affiliations</h4><div id="con1" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Navid A.</span> <span property="familyName">Zenooz</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Department of Radiology, Yale New Haven Hospital, 20 York St, New Haven, CT 06510 (N.A.Z.); the Department of Radiology, University of California, Los Angeles, Calif (R.H., J.P.F.); the Department of Radiology, Grand Rapids Medical Education and Research Center, Grand Rapids, Mich (L.M.); and the Department of Radiology, University Medical Center, Case Western Reserve University, Cleveland, Ohio (R.C.G.). Presented as an education exhibit at the 2007 RSNA Annual Meeting. Received May 5, 2008; revision requested July 15 and received January 16, 2009; accepted January 29. J.P.F. is a research consultant for Siemens and belongs to the speakers bureau of Bayer; R.C.G. receives research support from General Electric and Siemens; all other authors have no financial relationships to disclose.</span></div></div><div class="core-author-link"><a href="/authored-by/Zenooz/Navid+A" rel="nofollow">View all articles by this au